        <prompt>What was the significance of Social Darwinism in American society?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">It provided a scientific-sounding justification for social and economic inequality</option>
            <option letter="b">It promoted social welfare programs</option>
            <option letter="c">It advocated for government regulation</option>
            <option letter="d">It supported labor unions</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Social Darwinism, promoted by Herbert Spencer and others, applied evolutionary concepts to society, justifying economic inequality and opposition to social reform as natural selection.</explanation>
