    <question>
        <prompt>How did the concept of the "self-made man" influence American business culture?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">It promoted individualism and justified the wealth of successful businessmen</option>
            <option letter="b">It emphasized collective achievement</option>
            <option letter="c">It supported government intervention</option>
            <option letter="d">It criticized business success</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The "self-made man" ideal celebrated individual achievement and was used to justify the enormous wealth of successful businessmen while downplaying structural advantages and inherited privilege.</explanation>
