        <prompt>What role did Andrew Carnegie's "Gospel of Wealth" play in American philanthropy?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">It established the idea that wealthy individuals had an obligation to use their money for social good</option>
            <option letter="b">It encouraged wealth hoarding</option>
            <option letter="c">It promoted government welfare programs</option>
            <option letter="d">It focused on personal luxury</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Carnegie's "Gospel of Wealth" argued that wealthy individuals had a moral obligation to use their money to improve society, establishing a model for modern philanthropic giving.</explanation>
    </question>
